  "slug": "extra-crispy-chicken-wraps",
  "title": "Extra Crispy Chicken Wraps",
  "subtitle": "Breaded chicken thighs fried crisp, with bacon, cheddar, and salad in a flour tortilla",
  "excerpt": "Butterflied chicken breasts coated in spiced panko and shallow-fried until very crunchy, then layered with bacon, cheese, tomato, and crispy fried onions in a tortilla wrap. Four wraps from two chicken breasts.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Panko-crumbed chicken, shallow-fried, gives you a crunch that holds up inside the wrap. The spice mix splits between the flour and the breadcrumbs so flavour goes all the way through the coating. The fried onions, made in the same oil, are worth the extra two minutes."
          }
        ]
