      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set out three bowls: the first with the flour, the second with the beaten egg and milk, the third with the panko breadcrumbs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mix the paprika, 1 tsp salt, oregano, garlic powder, onion powder, and black pepper together in a small bowl. Stir half into the flour and the other half into the breadcrumbs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Butterfly each chicken breast through the middle to make 4 even pieces. Coat each one in the flour, then the egg, then the breadcrumbs, pressing firmly at each stage."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat 250 ml of vegetable oil in a large frying pan over medium heat until a breadcrumb dropped in sizzles immediately. Use tongs to lower the chicken in. Fry for 4 to 5 minutes per side until golden brown and cooked through the centre. Rest on kitchen paper. Lay a slice of cheese on each piece while still hot and let it melt slightly, then slice into strips."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Toss the onion slices in the leftover flour, shake off the excess, and fry in the same oil until golden and crispy, turning occasionally."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stack in the centre of each tortilla. Spoon on a tablespoon of sweet chilli sauce. Add a lettuce leaf, 4 slices of tomato, 2 rashers of bacon, the chicken strips, and a handful of crispy onions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fold up the bottom, then roll tightly. If the wrap feels loose, secure the base with a strip of foil to hold everything in."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Baked version: leave the chicken uncut, toss in the coatings, then bake on a tray at 200°C fan until crispy, turning halfway. Slice into strips before assembling."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Make sure the oil is hot enough before adding the chicken. A breadcrumb should sizzle immediately on contact.",
              "cause": "Oil not hot enough; coating absorbs oil rather than crisping.",
              "symptom": "Coating is soft and greasy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Press the breadcrumbs firmly onto the chicken at every stage. Wet the surface with egg before the panko.",
              "cause": "Coating not pressed on firmly, or egg wash skipped.",
              "symptom": "Coating falls off during frying"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use a probe thermometer; chicken breast is done at 74°C in the centre. Reduce heat and cover the pan for the last minute if the outside is browning too fast.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle cooked.",
              "symptom": "Outside is golden but inside is pink"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat on a wire rack in a hot oven (200°C fan) for 8 minutes rather than microwaving.",
              "cause": "Microwaved or reheated in a covered pan.",
              "symptom": "Leftovers lost their crunch"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Spicier coating: add a pinch of cayenne or chilli powder to the spice mix."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sauce swap: swap the sweet chilli for sriracha mayo or a garlic yoghurt."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best assembled fresh. The fried chicken keeps two days in the fridge; reheat on a rack in a hot oven to restore the crunch before building the wraps."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
